description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band 6 Respiratory Nurse Specialist in - Cystic Fibrosis, Primary Ciliary Dyskinesia and Bronchiectasis&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for a dynamic and enthusiastic Band 6 Clinical Nurse Specialist with a special interest in Cystic Fibrosis, Bronchiectasis and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Primary Ciliary Dyskinesia (PCD) &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;to join our team&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post offers an exciting opportunity to join an experienced multidisciplinary team providing high quality care to young adults with chronic complex lung conditions. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful applicant will manage a case load of patients and provide care to patients in the community, inpatient and outpatient setting. You will be working alongside a specialist team of medical, physiotherapy and dietetic staff, to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;deliver highly specialist care in the assessment and treatment of patients with CF, PCD and Bronchiectasis, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;including facilitation of the successful transition of patients from paediatric to adult care. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Leeds Centre for Cystic Fibrosis is recognised as a leader in CF care, the unit has expanded over recent years providing care for over 400 adult patients within the specialty. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The newly established Adult PCD service will provide expert care for adults with PCD through local and regional clinics. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful applicant will possess excellent communication and organisational skills, embrace change and demonstrate a willingness and aptitude to drive the service forward. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Experience in Cystic Fibrosis is not essential as full support and mentorship will be given. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;All applicants must have a minimum of 18 months experience at band 5 level, hold a Supported Learning in Practice qualification or equivalent and possess an up to date driving licence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information please contact senior Charge Nurse Jason Swarbrooke&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
